00:16:57.850 --> 00:16:59.818 line:95%,end
We know!
We know how you work.

00:16:59.885 --> 00:17:03.088 line:95%,end
-That feels ridiculous.
-We're saying we're a team.

00:17:03.155 --> 00:17:05.290 line:95%,end
Well, you can go be a team
at another dance studio,

00:17:05.357 --> 00:17:08.827 line:95%,end
because at this studio,
it's my way or the highway.

00:17:08.894 --> 00:17:10.629 line:95%,end
(suspenseful music playing)


00:17:14.333 --> 00:17:16.268 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: We're saying
that we're a team, and...

00:17:16.335 --> 00:17:18.303 line:95%,end
Well, you can go be a team
in another dance studio,

00:17:18.370 --> 00:17:21.807 line:95%,end
because at this studio,
it's my way or the highway.

00:17:22.674 --> 00:17:23.642 line:95%,end
That's it.

00:17:23.709 --> 00:17:24.777 line:95%,end
I've made up my mind.

00:17:24.843 --> 00:17:27.679 line:5%,start
If we can't walk in there
national champions

00:17:27.746 --> 00:17:30.449 line:5%,start
with a number that I know can win,

00:17:30.516 --> 00:17:31.750 line:95%,end
<i>then I don't want to go.</i>

00:17:31.817 --> 00:17:33.052 line:95%,end
So, we are the National winners.

00:17:33.118 --> 00:17:34.553 line:95%,end
I don't want to tarnish that reputation.

00:17:35.187 --> 00:17:37.156 line:95%,end
Maddie is their national title winner.

00:17:37.222 --> 00:17:38.991 line:95%,end
I don't want her to look bad.

00:17:39.058 --> 00:17:40.659 line:95%,end
And Gianna is going to go.

00:17:40.726 --> 00:17:42.027 line:95%,end
My name will not be on the number.

00:17:42.494 --> 00:17:44.229 line:95%,end
HOLLY:
<i>So first it was, the group was not going.</i>

00:17:44.296 --> 00:17:47.066 line:5%,start
Now the group is going,
but the group can only go

00:17:47.132 --> 00:17:49.101 line:95%,end
<i>if her name is removed</i>

00:17:49.168 --> 00:17:50.969 line:95%,end
<i>and she's not doing any choreography.</i>

00:17:51.036 --> 00:17:53.305 line:95%,end
And that's the ultimate slap
in the face for the girls.

00:17:53.372 --> 00:17:55.307 line:95%,end
Gianna is willing to
come in tomorrow morning...

00:17:56.041 --> 00:17:58.610 line:95%,end
and rehearse for four hours
before you get on the bus.

00:17:58.677 --> 00:18:00.279 line:95%,end
The mothers have made it quite clear

00:18:00.345 --> 00:18:02.114 line:95%,end
that they think that their kids
are amazing

00:18:02.181 --> 00:18:03.549 line:5%,start
with or without Brooke.

00:18:03.615 --> 00:18:04.983 line:5%,start
<i>If Gianna wants to</i>
<i>get up in the morning</i>

00:18:05.050 --> 00:18:08.420 line:95%,end
<i>and come here and work on</i>
<i>this number, that's fine.</i>

00:18:08.487 --> 00:18:13.025 line:95%,end
Because I cannot let Brooke
hold back these other dancers.

00:18:13.092 --> 00:18:17.830 line:95%,end
I would never let my child
shake her pompoms for some boy

00:18:17.896 --> 00:18:19.731 line:95%,end
to go to college for free.

00:18:19.798 --> 00:18:21.867 line:95%,end
I know that, Abby,
and I need her to make that decision

00:18:21.934 --> 00:18:22.768 line:95%,end
on her own.

00:18:22.835 --> 00:18:24.436 line:95%,end
ABBY: You make a commitment
in the beginning of the year,

00:18:24.503 --> 00:18:26.105 line:95%,end
you see it through
til the end of the year.

00:18:26.171 --> 00:18:28.974 line:95%,end
If you don't want to do it
again next year, that's fine.

00:18:29.041 --> 00:18:30.809 line:95%,end
There's integrity there.

00:18:30.876 --> 00:18:32.845 line:95%,end
<i>Brooke should have come and told me.</i>

00:18:32.911 --> 00:18:34.113 line:95%,end
Would I have been angry?

00:18:34.179 --> 00:18:37.616 line:95%,end
Yes, but it would have
been the right move

00:18:37.683 --> 00:18:40.119 line:95%,end
on her part and her parents.

00:18:40.185 --> 00:18:41.120 line:95%,end
Enough said.

00:18:41.186 --> 00:18:43.922 line:95%,end
(suspenseful music playing)

00:18:45.324 --> 00:18:46.792 line:5%,start
("Sentimental"
by Nikko Lowe playing)

00:18:46.859 --> 00:18:49.728 line:5%,start
GIANNA: In, out.
Releve. Leg high.

00:18:49.795 --> 00:18:52.698 line:5%,start
MADDIE: <i>I don't really think it's that</i>
<i>stressful not having Brooke.</i>

00:18:52.764 --> 00:18:57.136 line:5%,start
She finally got a chance to
be like the star of the group dance.

00:18:57.202 --> 00:19:00.038 line:95%,end
<i>And now I feel bad</i>
<i>because I'm doing it.</i>

00:19:01.807 --> 00:19:04.510 line:95%,end
PAIGE: <i>I feel bad that Brooke</i>
<i>has to make this decision,</i>

00:19:04.576 --> 00:19:07.212 line:5%,start
but I'll support her any way she wants

00:19:07.279 --> 00:19:09.715 line:5%,start
to go because she's my sister.

00:19:09.781 --> 00:19:11.783 line:95%,end
-Thank you, Gia.
-Where did you want our tag?

00:19:11.850 --> 00:19:13.018 line:95%,end
NIA: <i>Keep believing Miss Abby.</i>

00:19:13.085 --> 00:19:15.687 line:5%,start
We can pull it off and we'll win, still.

00:19:15.754 --> 00:19:16.922 line:95%,end
(inspirational music playing)

00:19:16.989 --> 00:19:19.725 line:95%,end
HOLLY: Hey, girls!
How was rehearsal?

00:19:19.791 --> 00:19:21.460 line:95%,end
Gianna leading the troops.

00:19:21.527 --> 00:19:23.462 line:95%,end
<i>I arrive at the studio</i>
<i>to go on the bus.</i>

00:19:23.529 --> 00:19:24.530 line:95%,end
There's no Abby.

00:19:24.596 --> 00:19:26.498 line:95%,end
<i>I'm feeling pretty relaxed.</i>

00:19:27.065 --> 00:19:28.901 line:95%,end
This could work out okay.

00:19:28.967 --> 00:19:30.402 line:95%,end
ALL: Move that bus!

00:19:30.469 --> 00:19:31.303 line:95%,end
(laughing)

00:19:31.370 --> 00:19:32.704 line:95%,end
ALL: Move that bus!

00:19:32.771 --> 00:19:34.006 line:95%,end
But why can't you let me sit?

00:19:34.072 --> 00:19:35.607 line:95%,end
GIRL: Mom, come back through.

00:19:35.674 --> 00:19:37.009 line:95%,end
(screaming)

00:19:37.075 --> 00:19:38.310 line:95%,end
(dramatic music playing)

00:19:38.377 --> 00:19:39.645 line:95%,end
GIRL: Wait, Abby's here!

00:19:39.711 --> 00:19:40.812 line:95%,end
MELISSA: No way!

00:19:40.879 --> 00:19:43.982 line:95%,end
-Oh, my gosh!
-MADDIE: Pretend you're sleeping!

00:19:44.049 --> 00:19:46.151 line:95%,end
(yelling)

00:19:46.218 --> 00:19:48.487 line:95%,end
Oh, why's she here?

00:19:49.521 --> 00:19:50.889 line:95%,end
Oh, that just ruined my weekend.

00:19:50.956 --> 00:19:51.890 line:95%,end
Give me your (indistinct)

00:19:51.957 --> 00:19:52.991 line:95%,end
ABBY: Hello, everybody.

00:19:53.058 --> 00:19:54.426 line:95%,end
GIRL: Hi Ab.

00:19:54.493 --> 00:19:57.930 line:95%,end
I have decided to go
because you have no idea

00:19:57.996 --> 00:20:00.098 line:95%,end
what it's going to be like
in New Jersey, number one.

00:20:00.165 --> 00:20:02.367 line:95%,end
I really didn't want to get on the bus,

00:20:03.035 --> 00:20:05.604 line:95%,end
but I could not throw Gianna
to the wolves.

00:20:05.671 --> 00:20:07.072 line:95%,end
<i>She does not deserve that.</i>

00:20:07.139 --> 00:20:08.574 line:95%,end
Kelly is not here?

00:20:10.709 --> 00:20:13.512 line:95%,end
<i>You really know what person</i>
<i>is important in your house, don't you?</i>

00:20:13.579 --> 00:20:16.148 line:95%,end
HOLLY: <i>Those feelings of euphoria</i>
<i>were short-lived.</i>

00:20:17.249 --> 00:20:19.251 line:95%,end
What a way to start a trip.

00:20:19.318 --> 00:20:20.953 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:20:21.019 --> 00:20:23.055 line:95%,end
ABBY: Bus driver Jim!

00:20:23.121 --> 00:20:24.556 line:95%,end
Are we there yet?

00:20:25.991 --> 00:20:27.626 line:95%,end
-WOMAN: I think right there.
-WOMAN: What do you want to do, like--

00:20:27.693 --> 00:20:28.827 line:95%,end
-WOMAN: Just put a line.
-WOMAN: Like here?

00:20:28.894 --> 00:20:29.728 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Yep.

00:20:29.795 --> 00:20:31.964 line:95%,end
MELISSA: This is Cathy
from Candy Apple that's calling me.

00:20:32.030 --> 00:20:34.166 line:95%,end
-ABBY: No!
-JILL: No!

00:20:34.233 --> 00:20:35.434 line:95%,end
-No way!
-Second time.

00:20:35.500 --> 00:20:37.669 line:95%,end
ABBY: Do not give her any information.

00:20:37.736 --> 00:20:39.171 line:95%,end
Why is she calling you?

00:20:39.238 --> 00:20:40.906 line:95%,end
That is so unethical.

00:20:40.973 --> 00:20:41.873 line:95%,end
Hi!

00:20:41.940 --> 00:20:43.275 line:95%,end
How often does she call her?

00:20:44.009 --> 00:20:46.678 line:5%,start
Melissa gets this phone call
from Cathy of all people.

00:20:46.745 --> 00:20:48.213 line:5%,start
Why does Cathy have your number?

00:20:48.280 --> 00:20:50.015 line:95%,end
CATHY: <i>I was thinking maybe</i>
<i>there would be a time</i>

00:20:50.082 --> 00:20:51.416 line:95%,end
<i>that we could get the girls together.</i>

00:20:51.483 --> 00:20:52.818 line:95%,end
<i>Maybe meet halfway somewhere?</i>

00:20:52.884 --> 00:20:54.720 line:95%,end
Okay. Sounds good.

00:20:54.786 --> 00:20:58.223 line:95%,end
I can't believe that Melissa
is talking to her like that.

00:21:02.261 --> 00:21:04.196 line:95%,end
MELISSA:
Are you going to a competition?

00:21:04.263 --> 00:21:06.465 line:95%,end
CATHY: <i>We are,</i>
<i>we're going to a competition.</i>

00:21:06.531 --> 00:21:08.767 line:95%,end
<i>We're heading to, um, New Jersey.</i>

00:21:09.935 --> 00:21:10.902 line:95%,end
MELISSA: Oh, you are.

00:21:10.969 --> 00:21:13.905 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>I am livid because Cathy's</i>
<i>on her way to New Jersey,</i>

00:21:13.972 --> 00:21:16.608 line:95%,end
and she's going to show up again
with these older kids

00:21:16.675 --> 00:21:20.512 line:95%,end
who are more Brooke's age
than they are Maddie's age.

00:21:20.579 --> 00:21:21.713 line:95%,end
<i>And Brooke won't be there.</i>

00:21:21.780 --> 00:21:24.082 line:95%,end
Okay. Bye!

00:21:24.149 --> 00:21:27.586 line:95%,end
ABBY: Do not let her know
that Brooke is not in this number,

00:21:27.653 --> 00:21:30.155 line:95%,end
because she will have a field day
with that.

00:21:30.222 --> 00:21:33.425 line:95%,end
Of all weeks for Brooke
to go for cheerleading tryouts,

00:21:33.492 --> 00:21:35.560 line:95%,end
you know the Candy Apples,
they're coming for blood.

00:21:35.627 --> 00:21:36.662 line:95%,end
They want to beat us.

00:21:36.728 --> 00:21:38.563 line:95%,end
And this may be an opportunity for them

00:21:38.630 --> 00:21:41.500 line:95%,end
because we were blocked
getting on the bus.

00:21:41.566 --> 00:21:44.036 line:95%,end
<i>I hate to say it,</i>
<i>but this could be Cathy's week.</i>

00:21:44.102 --> 00:21:45.537 line:95%,end
ABBY:
I'm telling you one thing.

00:21:45.604 --> 00:21:48.540 line:95%,end
That Candy Appple lady,
I don't care what she does.

00:21:48.607 --> 00:21:50.175 line:95%,end
She better not beat you.

00:21:50.242 --> 00:21:52.044 line:95%,end
Because you think I'm mad
at Brooke now, just wait.

00:21:52.110 --> 00:21:53.412 line:95%,end
If that woman wins,

00:21:53.478 --> 00:21:56.748 line:95%,end
Brooke's hide'll be hanging off the top
of that balcony at that studio.

00:21:56.815 --> 00:21:59.251 line:95%,end
(suspenseful music playing)


00:22:00.452 --> 00:22:02.287 line:95%,end
(upbeat music playing)

00:22:02.354 --> 00:22:05.924 line:5%,start
ABBY: <i>We're traveling to Starbound</i>
<i>in Nutley, New Jersey.</i>

00:22:06.825 --> 00:22:08.293 line:5%,start
(indistinct)

00:22:08.360 --> 00:22:09.995 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>We are the reigning</i>
<i>national winners.</i>

00:22:10.062 --> 00:22:11.596 line:95%,end
<i>That's what we won at Lake Tahoe.</i>

00:22:11.663 --> 00:22:15.801 line:95%,end
<i>There are people at Starbound</i>
<i>who are expecting to see more.</i>

00:22:15.867 --> 00:22:18.303 line:95%,end
-Ready to do some dancing?
-(indistinct chatter)

00:22:18.370 --> 00:22:21.440 line:95%,end
ABBY: <i>We need to walk in there</i>
<i>and show them that we've grown.</i>

00:22:21.506 --> 00:22:23.275 line:5%,start
So there's a lot at stake.

00:22:23.342 --> 00:22:25.077 line:95%,end
WOMAN: Want her to wear those?
Okay. Perfect.

00:22:28.780 --> 00:22:30.749 line:95%,end
HOLLY: I think it looks nice
and sophisticated plain.

00:22:30.816 --> 00:22:31.850 line:95%,end
-WOMAN: Thank you.
-ABBY: All right, girls,

00:22:31.917 --> 00:22:33.618 line:95%,end
remember, this is Starbound.

00:22:33.685 --> 00:22:36.088 line:95%,end
You are their national winners.

00:22:36.154 --> 00:22:38.423 line:95%,end
You can't be any less than that,
do you understand?

00:22:38.490 --> 00:22:39.424 line:95%,end
ALL: Yes.

00:22:39.491 --> 00:22:41.059 line:95%,end
Remember, Brooke never existed.

00:22:41.126 --> 00:22:42.861 line:95%,end
They have no idea
we're missing a dancer.

00:22:42.928 --> 00:22:46.098 line:95%,end
We cannot and will not

00:22:46.164 --> 00:22:48.533 line:95%,end
have little mistakes like that.

00:22:48.600 --> 00:22:50.736 line:95%,end
You cannot afford it this weekend.

00:22:50.802 --> 00:22:51.636 line:95%,end
Does everyone...

00:22:51.703 --> 00:22:53.505 line:95%,end
CHRISTI: <i>The pressure on the girls</i>
<i>this week is tremendous.</i>

00:22:53.572 --> 00:22:55.273 line:5%,start
They're going to need a back brace
by the end of the week

00:22:55.340 --> 00:22:56.875 line:95%,end
<i>with all the pressure</i>
<i>Abby is putting on their shoulders.</i>

00:22:56.942 --> 00:22:58.577 line:95%,end
<i>Like, you must win.</i>
<i>You must be fabulous.</i>

00:22:58.643 --> 00:23:00.345 line:95%,end
You must be. You must be.
You must be.

00:23:01.480 --> 00:23:04.583 line:95%,end
CATHY: We have our...

00:23:04.649 --> 00:23:06.651 line:95%,end
nemesis here again this week.

00:23:06.718 --> 00:23:08.687 line:95%,end
-How did that happen?
-ALL: Boo.

00:23:08.754 --> 00:23:10.021 line:95%,end
The Abby Lee Dance Company.

00:23:10.088 --> 00:23:11.423 line:95%,end
Boo.

00:23:11.490 --> 00:23:14.693 line:95%,end
We cannot get beat
by a hokeypokey number again.

00:23:14.760 --> 00:23:16.361 line:95%,end
It's just not going to be good for us.

00:23:17.028 --> 00:23:19.765 line:95%,end
Do not talk to them backstage.

00:23:19.831 --> 00:23:22.033 line:95%,end
Do not let her psych you out.

00:23:22.100 --> 00:23:25.270 line:95%,end
So, lucky us, we get to see
those Candy Apples again.

00:23:25.337 --> 00:23:27.139 line:95%,end
I'm not going to start anything
with Cathy,

00:23:27.205 --> 00:23:28.840 line:95%,end
but certainly if Cathy starts with me,

00:23:28.907 --> 00:23:30.375 line:95%,end
I'm not backing down from Cathy.

00:23:30.442 --> 00:23:32.144 line:95%,end
JILL: I just don't appreciate
all the low blows

00:23:32.210 --> 00:23:33.412 line:95%,end
she did with MacKenzie.

00:23:33.478 --> 00:23:35.213 line:95%,end
She did low blows with Chloe.

00:23:35.280 --> 00:23:37.883 line:95%,end
She's a low blower.
Like, if--if my nose is so...

00:23:37.949 --> 00:23:39.851 line:95%,end
She's a low blower!

00:23:39.918 --> 00:23:41.286 line:95%,end
She is a low blower.

00:23:41.353 --> 00:23:42.454 line:95%,end
Is Mackenzie ready?

00:23:42.521 --> 00:23:44.189 line:95%,end
ABBY: Yes, Mackenzie's ready.

00:23:44.256 --> 00:23:46.458 line:95%,end
Straight legs, pointed feet,
shoulders down.

00:23:46.525 --> 00:23:48.460 line:95%,end
If you forget, stay backstage.

00:23:48.527 --> 00:23:49.394 line:95%,end
Don't come out.

00:23:49.461 --> 00:23:51.229 line:95%,end
Because I'm going to chop
your head off. Go!

00:23:51.296 --> 00:23:54.366 line:95%,end
-(crowd cheering)
-(intense music playing)

00:23:54.433 --> 00:23:56.601 line:95%,end
Who's gonna take my boots?

00:23:56.668 --> 00:23:59.704 line:5%,start
I'm very nervous that MacKenzie's
going to forget her solo on stage,

00:23:59.771 --> 00:24:02.474 line:95%,end
<i>and I don't think</i>
<i>she's just going to ad lib.</i>

00:24:02.541 --> 00:24:05.310 line:95%,end
I think she'll just run off
the stage if she forgets.

00:24:05.377 --> 00:24:07.379 line:95%,end
-Smile. Okay?
-Okay!

00:24:07.446 --> 00:24:08.480 line:95%,end
Have fun.

00:24:08.547 --> 00:24:10.482 line:5%,start
There's one part in my dance
that's really hard.

00:24:10.549 --> 00:24:11.983 line:5%,start
It's a round of back handspring.

00:24:12.050 --> 00:24:14.386 line:95%,end
<i>I'm going to show everyone</i>
<i>that I'm the best.</i>

00:24:15.020 --> 00:24:16.655 line:95%,end
ANNOUNCER: <i>(indistinct)</i>
<i>next up to the stage.</i>

00:24:16.721 --> 00:24:18.924 line:95%,end
<i>Ages 7 and 8, number 321.</i>

00:24:18.990 --> 00:24:21.660 line:95%,end
(intense music playing)

00:24:21.726 --> 00:24:24.729 line:5%,start
(jazz music playing)

00:24:55.494 --> 00:24:58.096 line:95%,end
(crowd cheering)

00:24:58.163 --> 00:25:00.432 line:95%,end
Yay, Mackenzie!

00:25:00.499 --> 00:25:03.034 line:95%,end
MacKenzie nailed her side aerials

00:25:03.101 --> 00:25:05.537 line:95%,end
and, you know, she nailed
that back handspring, too.

00:25:05.604 --> 00:25:08.340 line:95%,end
So she's really come a long way
in a short amount of time.

00:25:09.040 --> 00:25:12.844 line:95%,end
You know, ladies, that this row
was reserved for us, just FYI.

